From e4abb0363242cd5fd8d89ce93b6de96b0df6ac94 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 16:41:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] SYNC ALL: VIN-match opt-in toggle + loud ECM/PCM
 SKIM-disabled warning
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DumpsTabV2: add a 'Match VINs + recompute checksums' checkbox next to SYNC
ALL. Checked (default) = write VIN+CRC to BCM/RFH/PCM and sync security
(legacy behavior); unchecked = security-only sync, VINs untouched. The VIN-
required gate relaxes when matching is off. Engine already separated VIN from
security (engWriteBcmVin/RfhVin/PcmVin); this just surfaces the choice.

crossValidate: make the GPEC2A/ECM SKIM-disabled (0x00/0x02) condition loud —
explicit message that the engine module ignores the secret and starts
regardless (extra-loud when SEC6 reads as paired, the deceptive case). Kept
as a WARNING, not an export-blocking issue (SKIM default is legitimate; the
SEC6 writers never touch it) — verified against exportSafetyGate.

26 DumpsTab + 20 crossValidate/exportSafety tests green.
